### WARNING
### This file changes local development data.
### Requests are additive and may create orders, payments, reservations and stock movements.
### Flows are designed to finish in terminal states and avoid active dangling reservations.
### Creating an order through this file loads product snapshots from Catalog and allocates Inventory stock.
### Succeeding a payment marks the order as Paid and commits Inventory reservation.
### Failed payment flow uses a fake order id to avoid Inventory side effects.
### Ordering API must be running and configured through CatalogApi:BaseUrl and InventoryApi:BaseUrl.
### Change runId before running the full flow again.

@PaymentApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5206
@OrderingApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5172
@InventoryApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5245

@runId = 001

@productVariantId = 9572fb9d-f059-401e-9041-7fc75f8cb414
@sku = ARM-BLK


### Health check
GET {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/health


### Check Inventory stock before flow
GET {{InventoryApi_HostAddress}}/api/stock/{{sku}}


### Create order and allocate Inventory stock
# @name createOrder
POST {{OrderingApi_HostAddress}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Payment Flow Customer {{runId}}",
  "customerEmail": "payment-flow-{{runId}}@example.com",
  "items": [
    {
      "productVariantId": "{{productVariantId}}",
      "quantity": 2
    }
  ]
}


### Get created order details
@orderId = {{createOrder.response.body.$.id}}

GET {{OrderingApi_HostAddress}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}


### Check Inventory stock after order reservation
GET {{InventoryApi_HostAddress}}/api/stock/{{sku}}


### Create payment for order
# @name createPayment
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{orderId}}",
  "amountMinor": 13800,
  "currency": "USD",
  "provider": "Manual"
}


### Get created payment details
@paymentId = {{createPayment.response.body.$.id}}

GET {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}


### Mark payment as succeeded
### This should mark the order as Paid and commit Inventory reservation.
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/succeed
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "providerReference": "MANUAL-APPROVED-{{runId}}"
}


### Get payment details after succeed
GET {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}


### Get order details after payment succeed
GET {{OrderingApi_HostAddress}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}


### Check Inventory stock after payment succeed
GET {{InventoryApi_HostAddress}}/api/stock/{{sku}}


### Mark already succeeded payment as succeeded again should return 400
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/succeed
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "providerReference": "MANUAL-APPROVED-RETRY-{{runId}}"
}


### Create payment for failed flow
### This uses a fake order id to avoid creating Inventory reservations.
# @name createPaymentForFail
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "amountMinor": 13800,
  "currency": "USD",
  "provider": "Manual"
}


### Mark payment as failed
@paymentToFailId = {{createPaymentForFail.response.body.$.id}}

POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentToFailId}}/fail
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "failureReason": "Manual failure {{runId}}"
}


### Get payment details after fail
GET {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentToFailId}}


### Mark already failed payment as succeeded should return 400
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/{{paymentToFailId}}/succeed
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "providerReference": "MANUAL-APPROVED-AFTER-FAIL-{{runId}}"
}


### Create invalid payment without order id should return 400
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "amountMinor": 13800,
  "currency": "USD",
  "provider": "Manual"
}


### Create invalid payment with zero amount should return 400
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{orderId}}",
  "amountMinor": 0,
  "currency": "USD",
  "provider": "Manual"
}


### Create invalid payment with invalid currency should return 400
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{orderId}}",
  "amountMinor": 13800,
  "currency": "US",
  "provider": "Manual"
}


### Create invalid payment without provider should return 400
POST {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{orderId}}",
  "amountMinor": 13800,
  "currency": "USD",
  "provider": " "
}


### Missing payment should return 404
GET {{PaymentApi_HostAddress}}/api/payments/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
